The idea I had when I re-wrote this SCP was that it chemically alters the subject at the molecular level, which would require a massive amount of energy for anything beyond the simplest of tasks. That's why the previous owner of it got himself killed - he was attempting what seemed to him to be a simple thing like , not realizing that the energy required to do so would kill him. Similarly, bringing a dead corpse back to life would require re-writing millions of dead cells into a living state, which causes whatever unspeakably redacted event that it did.







